RNA-Seq Training
----------------


This repository contains a 
1.subsampled RNA-seq dataset
2.metadata
3.resources - links to access sample FASTQ files, subesetted refrence genome and annotation
5. evaluation criteria
4.lecture slides
for practicing RNA-sequencing bioinformatics workflows. 


Get your sample data from the following link -
https://zenodo.org/records/7525740

The data originates from an epithelial-to-mesenchymal transition (EMT) study by *Yang et al. (2016)*.
- Control:   Day_0 - Uninduced epithelial cells (3 Replicates)
- Treatment: Day_7 - 7 days post-induction of EMT (3 Replicates)
- Sequencing Strategy: Paired-End (R1 and R2 files)
 This dataset represents approximately 0.5% of the original sequencing depth reads which map only to chr18 as modified by the original authors-
 (Gautheret, D. (2023, January 11). EMT RNA-seq dataset, subsampled. Zenodo. https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7525740)


You should have 12 `fastq.gz` files in your data directory, representing 6 biological samples with Paired-End sequencing.
